title: Wicked Witch
author: danielle and julia
text: i hear cackles echo in the sky,  i hope she is only passing by.   who cares about ghosts,  witches scare me the most.   that witch has evil powers,   that could turn me a lizard,  rat,  or flowers.   she can make nasty potions,   that can cause quite a commotion.   warts cover her crooked green nose,  she has a wicked appearance from her frizzy hair to her stubby toes.   just the thought of her being near,  makes my body shudder with fear.   the wind is whispering my name,  ah! are those her evil eyes staring at me through my window pane?  i close my eyes thinking this is just a nightmare,  when they open she will not be there.   i pull the covers over my face,  maybe if i go to sleep i will wake up with this all erased.   i hear more chuckling and screeching farther away,   is she gone? yes,  but she will be back to torment me next halloween day.

title: The Girl
author: devin
text: i remember the day,  i met the girl.  she had soft blue eyes,   with long brown hair.  she was so pretty,   and something told me,  that we were going to be really,  really,  really good friends.   as the months went along,  i became really close to her.  i had an empty feeling when i wasn't around her.  i seemed to have butterflies when i was around her.  one day we were talking under a tree and she told me that she really liked me.  i told her the same thing,  and we ended up hugging,  for a long time.  when we pulled the way,  i looked into her deep blue eyes that were trying to tell me something.  i nodded at the message,  moved in close towards her,  and pressed my lips against her soft,  pink lips.  it seemed to last an eternity,  yet it lasted only a few seconds.  we pulled away,  smiling,  and walked together,  hand in hand.

title: The Ballad of Oblivion
author: devynn
text: upon thy hand,  is but a grain of sand,  where hath thou been?  for there the men lay,  just for a short day,   with mind lost in oblivion.   you sit and you stare,  in your usual chair,  lost in thought with no hope.   as i watch in dismay,   in the park children play,  and i greatly loathe your apathy.   a knock on the door,  signifies there's more,  and you fear for your life and of death.   as i answer,  you lay still,  for you've taken a pill,  and tears swell in mine eyes.   they run and they yell,  under the witches black spell,  you have fallen in despair.   you started to sink,  i thought,  as i sipped my drink,  my bride,  never to return.

title: Human Rain
author: drew
text: raindrops fall down,   without a care.  teardrops are the same,  only with feeling.   it could be happiness,  or sadness.  it could be anger,  or jealousy.  tears come in many varieties.  but they all fall for a reason.   they fall from a person with eyes,  and a heart.   no one sheds tears for nothing.  there is a story inside every drop.   tears are books,  just told in a different way.  the way they fall,  and the sound they make.  those are the words,  of human rain.

title: Life is like a tree
author: dylan
text: life is like a tree,  in ways.   when you are born you are a little seed and when you are only a few months old you are a little sapling.  once you are a year old,  you are a teenage tree,  with branches reaching out as you get older,  bigger,  and taller,  you will do things like: when you cry,  you lose a leaf.  when you get scraped,  you break off bark.  when you break a bone,  you break off a branch.  but there is a good thing  when you have  children,  you drop  seeds which will live life like you did.  after a long life you will die or be chopped down,  but your saplings will live on repeating the same cycle  life is like a tree in many different ways.

title: Seasons Within Us
author: eileen
text: seasons,  seasons here they are,  to make us realize who we are.  we are unique and different inside,  but we still make up the world as one.  let us not forget  how the four seasons occur,  they separate on different paths but unite as one.  when spring arrives,  flowers start to grow and show.  when we as people start to develop,  we change and begin to excel at a skillful range.  we are really like spring and that is the real thing! not only spring we are the same,  we are also like summer.  the brightness of the sun makes nature rich and the perfect pitch of green.  many people have eyes green as the grass but soft as silk and others are dark as dirt but rich in soil.  i just hope the sun wont make me broil.  suddenley the weather will go cool with a slight brrr,  but don't worry its not winter,  it's the season fall! the leaves will fall on the eve of halloween  with unbelievable color schemes.  a symoblization of the nationalities  within the humanity around the world! our different cultures unite us together,  but when we divide, we fall.   just as the leaves stand tall and down fall.  eventually the heat of sun will go and its rays won't show.   this is the beginning of snow.  as i awake i see a snowflake on the lake.   there i knew there were no two snowflakes that looked the same.  even though we might have the same name,  it doesn't we're alike.  we might contain different personalities and specialities which makes us bright.  seasons,  seasons we are just like you and never forget it will stay true.

title: Deception
author: elliah
text: dusk.  a twich,  a glance.  lurking within shadows of  memory.   lurches to rid of remembrance.   he paces,  unknowing,  realizing.   the tipping point,  of heart and body,  shattered,  scattered,  removed from bonds  of iron-gold.   cold,  metallic taste,  enough to  crush through ivory lips.  impossible to  swallow.  strains to spit it out.   chokes.   stomach churning,  flickering movements,  scuttling like a fire burning  out.   he steps.   shivering violently,  understanding the brute force laid down by familiar arms,  reaching out,  to take back the  onslaught.   to no avail.   hunter-   hunted.

text: what i thought was reality,  was only a fantasy.  maybe what i made of it,  was not to be ignorant.  maybe i didn't show my true colors,  so that's my cue to go to my watercolors.  maybe i need to step it up a bit,  or just go back to writing my script.   maybe i was to vulnerable,  so i should go back to being tolerable.   maybe i got mixed up with the wrong crowd,  so i'll stand here being proud.  maybe my friends gave you the wrong ideas,  so i'll go back to sophia.  maybe i said those things,  but now i'll go back to playing my strings.   maybe i should have left before it begun,  but now i think you have won.  maybe you thought i was just your friend,  but to me you were my amend.   maybe i need to bring it to an end,  only because we were friends.   maybe it was all the haters,  who seemed to be like dictators.   maybe it was you who started this,  so i'll go sink into the abyss.    maybe that's quite it,  i need to let go a bit.

title: The Odd Cat
author: emily
text: when i awoke one morning,   a cat was on my head.  i    asked,  ''what are you doing there?''  it looked at me and said .  .  .   â“i find it rather irritating,   you have to be so rude.  for even though this is your head,  your manners are quite crudeâ”.   â“your nosiness is unnecessary,  your complaint did not need to be heard.  because for your information,  i am watching for a birdâ”.   â“the sneaky beast has once again,  tried to cheat while playing cards.  when comforted the rat snuck off,  and tried to hide in several yards. â”  i thought i must have not been feeling well,  or possibly hit my head.  for then a rather large gray mouse  had climbed up on my bed.   â“iâ’ve found him cat!â” he shouted,  as the cat jumped down beside him.  the mouse was wet from head to paw as if he had gone for a swim.   â“got sprayed by a hose, â” he said casually,  when jumping off the bed with the cat.  abruptly they both left me there alone,  staring at the wet part where he had sat.   to this day i donâ’t know what become of them,  but in their defense i never really tried.  i was still pretty fuming about the wet spot they left,  that never really seems to get dry.

title: The Poet
author: emma
text: i am the grass.   i am the soft green coating of a summer day.  i am the comforting landing to the harsh fall of snow.  i am the friend of all.  i am the grass  i am the hare i am the quick burst of energy across the open field.  i am the small witty creature that refuses to be caught.  i am the fear of grass.  i am the hare  i am the hawk i am the swift sail of power through the rough sky.  i am the dark object among the clouds that hunts with power.  i am the fear of the hare.  i am the hawk  i am the bear i am the brown tiger of the forest,  my stripes hidden.  i am the godlike hunter of the small wood.  i am the fear of the hawk.  i am the bear  i am man i am the beholder of the gun,  that hunts with stealth.  i am the strength of a pack,  that keeps to itself.  i am the fear of the bear.  i am man   i am the poet i am the beholder of the pen,  that hunts with the power of thought.  i am the hunter of the hunter,  holding my words close to me.  i am the fear of man,  pushing the boundaries of human thought.   i am the poet

title: Life of Frederick Douglass
author: emma
text: his name is frederick douglas,  who escaped the claws of slavery because of his abundance of bravery.   he fought long and hard for his freedom  when his master didnâ’t feed him.   beaten till he cannot stand,  slashes,  chains,  and whips until his soul was broken,  and not a word was heard from his lip.   one day it took a turn and his past began to burn.  he was taken to a welcoming farm  or as â“welcomingâ” as it could be.  he fought his strong urge to leave,  and he set his beaten soul free  education began to creep,  up in the young boy who had learned to leap.  reading and writing were a pleasant surprise which he decided to share with the rest of his guys    some days it was just too much he became so overwhelmed,  and he had to get in touch.  the other slaves were still stuck there but for him he couldn't bare.  and one the day in september all he could remember  was the slavery brutality and how such thing isn't considered cruelty.   douglass fled to new york state and on the date he became a free man,  in that free state

title: Can You Guess Who I Am?
author: eric
text: what is this mysterious animal? creeping through the underbrush.  stalking dinner,  large or small,  waiting to startle it with a rush.   with scent glands on tail,  i am armed with my locator.  my mate waits at home.  for i am bringing food for her.   i can mate but once a year.  when i hear something,   i turn a triangular ear.   howling to the moon,  i cry to the sky.  i call to my brothers.  the howl,  oh the howl,  it is my war cry.   sixty-three days after mating,  the pups are born.  the alpha may be the pup whoâ’s firstborn.   i am very sleek with many-colored fur.  when i go hunting,  often a catch does not occur.   i can run very fast,  but only for a short while.  sometimes my long snout looks like a wide smile.   padded feet run across the land.  like a dog,  my paw seems like a hand.   i love to run,  to jump and play.  i hunt in a pack,  sometimes we hunt all day.   the alpha male is the most powerful male.  when we have fights,  the alpha will prevail.   when the prey dies,  we have quite a feast.  we love to eat,  and chow down like a beast.   as little as two of us can begin a pack.  we bear a litter,  there is not much the pack will lack.   we create the hierarchy slowly at first.  then it speeds up,  we create with a thirst.   eventually we thrive and rule over the land.  sometimes we are feared,  this i donâ’t understand.   we are thought to be monsters by people widespread.  though the humans fear our bite,  it is our coming they dread.   what is this mysterious animal? creeping through the underbrush.  stalking dinner,  large or small waiting to startle it with a rush.   i am a wolf.  did you guess it? it all makes sense,  every last bit.

title: The Knock: Part II
author: eric
text: i sit at my desk and cry out with shock.  the knocks keep coming.  knock,  knock,  knock.   the clock has stopped now,  time is standing still.  but the knocks keep coming,  i wish i could take a sleeping pill.   it would stop the torture,   stop the pain.  outside i hear the noise of the rain.   the rain pours down,  hitting with a splash.  i have stopped working now.  lightning hits with a flash.   the school is silent,  not a sound in the halls.  i believe you could hear a pin,  if it falls.   it's just teacher and me,  alone.  i wish i could call someone with the telephone.   anyone could save us,  anyone at all.  i feel insignificant,  i feel so small.   what is this monster,  knocking at the door? please don't keep it up,  knock no more!  a rumble begins deep in my throat.  it sounds almost like a low,  musical note.   but wait! that sound is not coming from me.  it is coming from the ground! what is it?  let's wait and see.   my teacher hears it too,  she gives me a glance.  i shrug my shoulders,  and she goes into fighting stance.   it could be the evil,  the evil knocking at the door.  what if it is? at least it will knock no more.   i prepare myself for a fight,  as the sound increases.  as i wait for the evil,  my courage goes to pieces.   suddenly i can hear an explosion.  the room is torn in two.  horrible laughter can be heard all over.  trouble begins to brew.   i look to the teacher to see her reaction.  i suppose i am looking for some sort of distraction.   it doesn't come,  but the evil does.  the laughter grows.  i start to scream,  a very shrill scream.  my fear obviously shows.   suddenly i stop the scream,  without warning i stop.  the laughter stops for a minute.  maybe i will come out on top!  the teacher is yelling for help.  i tell the evil to come.  it laughs again,  but only once.  the sound makes my hands go numb.   a creature steps through the cursed door.  i tell it to come,  and it starts to roar.   time stops.

title: The Knock
author: eric
text: i sit in the chair and look up at the clock when will this end? then there comes a knock.   the teacher rises and goes to the door.  there is no one there,  as before.   every few minutes,  there is a knock on the door.  it is very annoying,  i gaze at the floor.   who could be there at the entrance to the room? outside the window,  the sky fills with gloom.   the raindrops come and hit with a splash.  when this period ends,  to the door i'll dash.   what is this knock? what does it mean? i look at my notebook and my face turns quite green.   i cannot explain it but there's something about the knock.  it fills me with dread.  i play with my sock.   the knock comes again,  and the teacher walks over.  her dress is patterned with a four-leaf clover.   this knock,  what is it? that makes me feel bad.  the rain comes down,  i put on the sweatshirt i had.   this horrible day,  what is happening? i wish the knocker would show itself so my fears don't take wing.   what horrible demon is at the door? who is knocking? will they knock more?  the teacher flings wide the door and calls into the hall ''is anyone there? anyone at all?''  there is no answer,  none at all.  no one answers,  from down the hall.   she goes to the desk and says with a grin ''we can't work today. ''  and the knock comes again.   her smile falters but only for a moment.  i start to wonder could this be an accident?  but no,  there is someone knocking at the door.  but there is no one there.  the teacher stomps her foot on the floor  ''who is doing this?'' she cries to the world.  ''who is knocking?'' my fears come unfurled.   ''it is a demon for sure!'' i say to the teacher.  ''a demon,  you agree? some unearthly creature. ''  ''it is driving us mad!'' i continue on.  ''i'm going crazy!'' and the rain pounds the lawn.   the knocks never stopped,  and there we sit today.  when?  when?  when? will the knocks go away?

text: the love i gave, the love that we share comes from our hearts the places where all of our romance take place.  the places where you take me to tell me you love me and you care about me but you don't.  i gave you the love that i would never give anyone else. you told me that you love me and you won't let anyone hurt me or take me away from you.  you told me that when the angels come for me you would be by my side.  now i realize why my friends wanted me to cheat on you or leave you and for you to find a life . but i told them i could't leave you because i love you.  i guess they were right and i were wrong i should of broke up with you.  you told me you gave me all the love in the world like i gave you. but to tell you the truth i never really saw the loving you gave me. i thought you gave me love because i wanted to see the love you had.  that's why they say fools fall in love well i am that fool falling in love with you

title: Writer's Block
author: erin
text: writer's block.  that time when you can't get an idea,  when you have no inspiration.  when your mind just doesn't want to work.  it's a time of great frustration.  i sit and sigh,  and wonder why,  i can't seem to write a thing.  i try to think of memories,  or things that inspire me,  but nothing comes to mind.  i sit and scribble on my paper,  or press random keys.  all the while thinking,  writer's block why have you chosen me?  writer's block.  i'll complete a story chapter,  and try to go on to the next.  but when i sit and try to write,  i just can't come up with anything.  i think about the idea,  that i had in mind.  and figure out that,  i can't write it well enough.  so then i sit and sigh,  and start to wonder why,  i can't seem to continue.  i try to think of things that inspire me,  but nothing comes to mind.  i sit a scribble on my paper,  or press random keys.  all the while thinking,  writer's block,  why have you chosen me?  writer's block.  right now i'm trying to write a poem,  and it isn't going well.  so i end up writing about,  the thing that's caught me in its grasp.  i sit and sigh,  and wonder why,  i can't seem to complete this assignment.  i try to think of memories,  or things that inspire me,  but nothing comes to mind.  i sit and scribble on my paper,  or press random keys.  all the while thinking,  writer's block,  why have you chosen me?  writer's block.  i've finally beaten you.  for you see,  i've finally completed this poem.  i sit and sigh,  and wonder why,  i had so much trouble.  i sat and scribbled on my paper,  and pressed random keys.  all the while thinking,  writer's block,  i've finally broken free!

title: Promises
author: faith
text: they are known to be kept not to be broken.  they play a big part in our lives,  they are used to comfort and assure us that something will be kept.    we really don't know how to keep promises and some of us don't know what they really are.  if we don't keep them we will hurt many peoples feelings because many people really believe in promises and they look forward for the promises to change their lives.  why don't we bother to keep them? that i do not know.    i surely don't know of a school which can teach us,  a book,  a teacher and a law that teaches how to keep them.  in keeping promises we need to work on it by ourselves.  i know of one thing that always fulfills its promises and that is today.  i asked today to give me a tomorrow and indeed i saw a tomorrow.    i don't know how to teach us how to keep them,  i only know of the sweet birds that chirp their sweet melodies in the bright,  shining,  summer morning or of lil romeo rapping about life to be understandable,  but i know not much about promises.  if only we could know how to keep them.    sometimes i wish that there were no promises ever but then i come to realize that promises belong to the world just like you and me.    i now realise that promises are not always broken but sometimes they are.

title: The Blind Man's Meal
author: felicia
text: introduction this poem was inspired by the painting by pablo piccaso called the ''blind man's meal. ''  the blind man walks alone through an endless night in the dark,  he is on his own trying to live life with all his might   he sits in solitude using his finger tips for eyes  while he blunders for his food.  he sits there and sighs  he wonders if its day  he wonders if its night  he always,  always prays  if he can have his sight  the blind man's meal told me how hard it must be  and how it must feel  not being able to see.

title: Life is. . .
author: gabriel
text: life is a little spark of time between two eternities.  it is a tragedy seen close-up but it is a comedy in the longshot. life is a happy,  content-to -stay bright flame almost never sput- tering until,  one day the pail of water known as death is poured upon it.  life is also brighter than the sun,  glorious- ly pure liquid that pulses through your veins,  your spirit,  even your very being.  life is a raging river flowing with an undescribably powerful current,  rushing into,  eroding, and passing over the obst- acles in what--when going through them seems like an eternity--but really pas- ses in the blink of god's eye. it is pla- nning,  hurrying,  making mistakes and as it  ends,  usually turning out for the best.  it's the sun shining onto,  and through a dome full of different colors,  and cascading the hues across the ground and entertaining the onlookers as the  colors form into a beautifully created  painting of joy and happiness.

title: The Bridge
author: gabriella
text: (this poem is based on bridge painting by monet)  in the peacefulness of my grandmother's garden i remember a beautiful painting  that i once saw  many years have passed,  since i have seen that painting yet the memories flood my mind  as clear as it were only yesterday  reflecting upon the thoughts of the painting causes me to reflect upon my passage from childhood,  to adolesence  i've crossed a few bridges and overcome a few obstacles on this journey in the years to come there will  be many more bridges to cross fondly,  i hope they will be remembered.

title: Old One
author: gavin
text: solitary,  old one sits atop a cap of sunken stone.  below a frothing flow snakes its way to sea.   time knows how long he stood.   old one's hands,  long and gnarled,  boughs twisted and turned,  trunk textured and mossy.   old one's leaves,  shiny,  glistening.   when stone he sat upon crumbled,  he stood.   when axe struck,  blade twisted,  handle snapped.   solitude knows the day he emerged from rich forest loam.  old,  plagued with mosses which hang from tired limbs like beards of many men who have come and gone.  birds perch on bumpy,  twisted shoulders.   squirrels live in craggy limbs.   beavers respect him.   for old one is the forest,  the forest would fail without him.   who is he? you ask,  why a not so solitary oak.

title: Growing Up Isn't As Fun As It Seems
author: haley
text: i broke down today. . .  i couldn't hold it in any longer.  all this pain.  misery.  regrets.  it all became too much for me to bear.  i haven't always been this way.  i used to be a vibrant child.  excited to grow up,  move out and start dating.  growing up wasn't exactly as i had imagined it would've been.  all of a sudden. . .  apple juice became alcohol.  suckers became cigarettes.  your best friends became your enemies.  sleepoers became all night parties. .  bruises and scrapped knees became broken hearts.  temporary tattoos became scars on wrists.  see what happened? i didn't want this.  as a matrter of fact,  i never asked for this.  i wanted my life to be an adventurous story. . .  not a surival one.

title: The Space to My Astronaut
author: hanna
text: if you are my sun,  am i then your planet? will you rise without fail to shine light on my day,  and then bring total black when you are gone? because you do,  bring light to my life,  and leave me blind in the darkness when you leave.  my world is nothing without you,  cold and unwanted.  if you are my sun,  am i quite important enough to get caught in your gravity? if so,  i will throw myself into orbit with glee.  am i important enough to get drawn in too close? will my mass be so large,  that i will burn in your beautiful rays? if so,  i will do so with a smile on my face,  and i will turn to nothing being the happiest planet there ever was.  this does happen in real life,  i throw myself in,  knowing iâ’ll get hurt,  but i do so with the biggest smile you will ever see on a broken heart.  so maybe iâ’m just an asteroid to your planet,  i spend my entire life racing towards you at thousands of miles an hour,  oblivious to the fact i will die before i reach my destination.  maybe you are the black hole to my galaxy,  youâ’re the center of my existence and draw me in till i die,  being ripped to shreds in an instant.  but,  paradoxically,  iâ’ll have a beautiful,  perfect world still going on once iâ’m caught in your trap.  nobody knows what will happen once you get sucked in a black hole,  but if it means i have a chance to be with you,  iâ’ll go through every black hole in the multiverse.  itâ’s weird,  everything you are,  kills me.  thatâ’s because,  my dear,  every moment without you,  i die a little more.  so be my sun that kills the planet with too much mass,  because that mass is the love i feel for you,  being drawn in ever closer.  be my planet that kills the asteroid,  because i have and will spend my whole life trying to reach you.  be the black hole to my galaxy,  because even though life goes on without you,  you will always suck me in.  be my supernova that no star can outshine,  be my dark matter that i will spend eternity trying to understand.  be my space,  my beautiful mystery that lures me in.  no matter what you are,  you will always be pulling me in.  and trust me,  no matter if i die every single time,  i will never resist.

title: Someone Should've Taught Him!
author: heather
text: i went to a birthday party today,  but i remembered what you said.  you told me not to drink and drive so i had a sprite instead.  i felt proud of myself the way you said i would that i didn't drink and drive though some friends said i should.   i knew i had made a healthy choice and that your advise to me was right.  as the party ended and the kids drove out of sight.   i got into my own car sure to get home in one peace.  never knowing what was coming something i expected least.   now i'm lying on the pavement,  i can hear the policeman say ''the guy that caused this wreck was drunk. '' his voice seemed far away.   my blood is all around as i try hard not to cry.  i can hear the paramedic say, ''this girl is going to die!'' i'm sure the guy had no idea while he was flying high,  because he made the choice to drink and drive that i would have to die.   so why do people do it? knowing it ruins lives? but now the pain is cutting me, like a hundred stabbing knives.  tell my sister not to be afraid,  tell daddy to be brave.  and when i go to heavan to put ''daddy's girl'' on my grave.   someone should have taught him that it's wrong to drink ad drive.  maybe if his mom and dad would have i'd still be alive.   my breath is getting short, i'm getting really scared.  these are my last moments and i'm so unprepared.   i wish you were here to hold me mommy,  as i lay here.  i wish i could say i love you and goodbye.

title: GROWING UP
author: hetvi
text: growing up is a trap,  trust me,  it is truly not my cup of tea.  a child is what i desire to be,  so that i get to be totally me.   getting up early is the worst thing; and going to school is just so boring! we eagerly wait for the last bell to ring,  we wait to reach home,  and dance and sing!  then come the just-so-tough studies,  leaving us no spare time for our buddies.  our time whiles away solving maths,  leaving us no time to burn our fats!  and then comes our love for fashion; admit it,  it truly is our passion! yet,  the school uniform makes it go crash! and so,  this too makes our day a trash.   but,  our perplexing emotions are the weirdest of all! they makes us wish we were just so tall.  at awkward times,  they make us cry,  but at times,  they too tell us to try and try.   growing up is a trap,  trust me,  it is truly not my cup of tea.  a child is what i desire to be,  so that i get to be totally me.

title: Little Bird
author: hiba
text: after i finished                                                                                    eating my donated scraps                                                                   i lied down on my thin mattress for an evening nap.                                  thought about my life                                                                          as sadly as everyday                                                                          especially after i deemed it useless to pray.                                            how i got so poor money and mind,  i canâ’t recall but i do know that i was in a constant brawl with myself  but then a little  bird came,  on my window sill she whispered,  â“iâ’ll tell you some news,  but you must sit still. â”  â“there is a human i know,  who is quite alright and the special thing about her is she can take flight. â”   i could not believe  what my ears might have just  heard and should i really trust this weirdly engaging bird?   â“how do i know that your little beak speaks the truth?â” and thatâ’s when she flew me high above my townâ’s roofs.   i flew way up high and above grand maple trees for once not minding the holes in my sleeves and my knees.   you would not believe what her lilâ’ wings had in store it was a beautiful sight not being at war with myself  eventually we landed,  in some strange kidâ’s yard and looked up to see her flying,  despite her mind scarred.      and when i squinted  i saw,  and grinning with glee,  the girl really smiling and flying,  looking so free.  is that me?  she downed to tell  me wind making noise like a fife that a bunch of bad days donâ’t mean you have a bad life.   â“you eat donations mattress you sleep on like straw but that should not be a reason for you to withdraw from yourself. â”  she also explained that that queer bird on the sill can make anybody fly by a sheer choice of will.   thatâ’s when i noticed i was no longer on ground but rather taking flight in the air,  no longer bound.   i felt so happy and for a moment i cried because for once in my life,  i felt side by side with myself

title: My Life in Thirteen Years
author: hikmeta
text: i was born on a very cold day on january 8,  1989.  i'm growing up,  thirteen years old,  and feeling ine.  i was born in bosnia and left at nine months old.  we lived in beautiful italy for eight years i'm told,  then off to a different germany for five years,  i hear.  when we left,  i was sad leaving family members so dear.  finally to a land of freedom,  the united states,  no fear.  i've been here for two years and five months with no tears.  i didn't know english on the first day of school.  kids tried to talk to me,  my conversation wasn't cool.  it was difficult to learn the way around the words.  i understood easy english so basic to kids.  now,  i'm good at english,  i know what i did.  i practiced and read books until i felt really good.  books are the key to learning,  just do it,  everyone should.  i have lots of friends in school,  they're full of fun.  i go to their house,  they come to mine; we can't wait to play in the sun.  i know how to cook so i made a cake,  and my aunt ate it all.  she liked it so much that when i bake she said to call.  i like computers because i get useful information.   it is great equipment and a wonderful invention.  i can read,  do reports,  and help my dad on his test.  it is a reflection of what life is,  nothing but the best.  ice skating,  volleyball,  and basketball are my sports.  my plans are to go to college and get a job,  of course.  i want to be a lawyer and be the best one in town.  to help those who need me to be supportive,  and come around.  my dad said if i become one,  he'd buy me a car,   so i can go to work,  shop,  and take trips really far.  michael jackson is my favorite singer and entertainer.  i like his songs,  he's cute,  and a great dancer.  my dream is to meet him one day on my birthday,  to tell him that i listen to him sing,  and feel a special way.  i'm glad that my family moved to this country to live.  we have lots of fun and have much love to give.  i dream of many things while living in america,  her land.  be patient dreams do come true,  yes they can!

title: Love Me. . . For Me. . .
author: izzi
text: car,  door,  rain. . .  love,  light,  shame. . . .  knife,  hand,  pain. . .  misunderstood all the same.  key,  piano,  solidarity,  yet i'm falling apart.  is there anyone to share with me,  the feelings from my heart.   is there anybody out there,  who  really understands how much weight some have to bear,  pressed upon their hands.  i long,  i lust,  i yearn,  i want.   i pine,  i crave,  i thirst,  i wine.  i wail,  i moan,  i weep,  i cry,  i sob,  i hark i want to die.  i ache,  i scream,  i burn,  i perish in the dark.  how many eyes,  how many ears,  that's what i seek to know,  to see the pain,   to hear the cries of loss,  as the hatred grows.   how many hearts were broken,  how many hearts forgotten and left stark,  how many hearts were left to rot,  how many in the dark? how many birds will fly above us,  how many months will last,  how many phases of the moon,  will fall into the past? how many shadows lost upon  the floor,  forever more to rest,   somewhere hidden in our core? they slip away through the paths  of time to rest in weary heights,   until none remember them dancing  with the lights.   the ground we walk on,  represents  the hearts stomped to the floor,  and how they build us,  so much  stronger than we were before.

title: Music of the night
author: james
text: night-time sharpens,  heightens each sensation .  .  .  darkness stirs and wakes imagination .  .  .  silently the senses abandon their defences .  .  .   slowly,  gently night unfurls its splendour .  .  .  grasp it,  sense it - tremulous and tender .  .  .  turn your face away from the garish light of day,  turn your thoughts away from cold,  unfeeling light - and listen to the music of the night .  .  .   close your eyes and surrender to your darkest dreams! purge your thoughts of the life you knew before! close your eyes,  let your spirit start to soar! and you'll live as you've never lived before .  .  .   softly,  deftly,  music shall surround you .  .  .  feel it,  hear it,  closing in around you .  .  .  open up your mind,  let your fantasies unwind,  in this darkness which you know you cannot fight - the darkness of the music of the night .  .  .   let your mind start a journey through a strange new world! leave all thoughts of the world you knew before! let your soul take you where you long to be ! only then can you belong to me .  .  .

title: Orange Bee

text: orange bee [:  earlier today,  i tripped over some clay.  next to it lied a bee.  he was in search of some tea.   i told him i could help him.  so he flew to the basket ball rim.  he asked if there was anything i need.  i said â“yes bee indeed. â”  i need some orange paint.  â“orange paint?â” asked the bee.  â“yes,  orange paint. â” i said.  â“what does it look like?â” asked the bee.   this color is just so bright.  for sure it entitles you for might.  tis rather squishy,  yet quite gooey.   it is very satisfying.  it can make you feel cheery,  it is oh so merry.  or at least thatâ’s how i feel.   â“mr.  bee i believe i have found you some tea. â” â“oh really? thank you!â” said the bee.  it tasted like a kind of berry.  could this perhaps be cherry?  i said yes bee it is.  he smiled and said lets find your paint.  and the bee did.  as the sun went down.   we enjoyed our last little bit of tea,  together we painted.  of everything that had inspired us.  and further on the year we grew as close friends.

title: The Streetlight
author: jasmine
text: the light is slightly dimmed,  as i sit here beneath it.  and i will sit here longer,  until i realize exactly why iâ’m sitting.   the light is being passed,  by cars with people in them.  and i still sit here waiting,   and being honked at by angry,  selfish drivers.   the light is being swarmed,  by a million specs of dust.  and i will stay here and wait,  until i know what iâ’m waiting for.   the light has made me realize,  that it is pointless to sit here and wait.  waiting gets you nowhere.  i need to take action.   the light is slowly fading,  as i get up and walk away.  and i will take action,  and go and make my way.

title: To say or Not to say ''I Love You''?
author: jennifer
text: what is love but an emotion that hurts more than internal wounds.  makes us do things that we don't usually do.   makes us lie.  makes us say things that shouldn't be heard by any mortals' ears,  but we still say them don't we dear?  we say things we don't usually mean.  love can hurt people like you and me.  don't say ''i love you'' unless you know what it means.  you may end up hurting people,   people me.   don't say ''i love you'',  or it may end up like a romance novel of shakspearian art.  romeo and juliet both died of a broken heart.   say ''i love you'' if that's what your heart wants say ''i love you'' if that's what you really want.  but be warned with love comes great sorrow.  don't say ''i love you'' if you can't bear the pain of hurting the people you for the most.   if you're sure it is true then take the risk! say ''i love you'' if it is true of heart.  they may end up saying ''i love you too.  from all of my heart!!''

title: Dance
author: jennifer
text: i watched with envy and greed.  i watched,  hearing the music,   and filled with an urgent need,   to jump out of my seat and perform with the elite dancers.   these dancers,  hardly older than i.   made it look effortless  and seemed to fly.  i  sat in a trance watching these people dance.  girls and boys about my age,  looked so lovely on that stage.   oh how i wish  i could fly like these birdlike dancers.  but alas i am stuck here,   a slippery fish.  oh the tears drizzle down my face.  and i cry  because i know i will never be able to take their place.

title: Never Forget

title: Home
author: jeslyn
text: outside my familyâ’s home.  i lay on the smooth grassy plains.  under a immense weeping willow tree,  with its long delicate leaves fluttering in the calm breeze.  past the willow tree there is a river.  i walk towards the river and gaze into the crystal-clear water.  within there is a tiny bird with its wing wedged between two rocks unable to fly away.  i kneel near the pleasant river to remove the rocks and the tiny bird is unafraid of me as it soars high into the heavenly sky,  above the grassy plains,  above the weeping willow tree,  until i am unable to see it.  beyond the grassy plains from outside my familyâ’s home i hear my mom calling for me to come inside the warm,  cozy home,  for it is getting too dark for me to see.  i walk away from the calming river,  past the massive weeping willow tree,  to my inviting home from where my mother is calling me from.  i am home.

title: My Angel Above
author: jilda
text: i walk into my grandmother's room and i immediately smell her aroma.  i lay down on her soft vacant bed and close my eyes.  i see her at the dinner table reminiscing about the past,  and secretly letting me take sips of wine from her glass.  i see her through the crack of her door,  on her bed yelling at allen iverson for not making a basket.  then i see her laying down,  resting so peacefully,  and so quiet,  with the moon peeking through her white linen drapes.  pictures of her grandchildren,  and family surrond the room.  i see her bob cut blonde hair and her big oval glasses.  tight stretch pants and oversized sweatshirts.  i see vivid flasbacks of the times we were together,  the times i looked at her,  the times i talked with her.  i can still taste her pound cake and all of her cookies,  no will be able to copy her baking habits.  i remember watching her at thanksgiving,  just to make sure that everyone was satisfied.  a tear sheds for every memory.  i hear the babies crying,  nana where are you? when the wind blows you can hear flowers whispering her name.  every tear drops so slowly on her pillow.  she would sing to me,  ''row,  row,  row your boat gently down the stream,  merely,  merely,  merely,  merely life is but a dream.  and i can see my grandmother in a boat with the angels escorting her to the golden gates,  wearing a straw hat and white gloves.  she whispers good-bye to me in her angelic voice and sets sail to heaven.

title: Conversations With My Son On the Boulevard
author: john
text: i awake to a cloudy and breezy november morning,  where the leaves are rustling by,  businesses starting to open,  as i start my day with my beloved son.   we walk the boulevard by our apartment,  in paris,  france.  this boulevard is packed and crowded by lunch with people enjoying brunch at a local bistro,  however, it is deserted in the early morning.  it is like my son and i are the only two people on the earth.   in the morning,  it is calm and laid back.  with this,  my son and i have great conversations,  discussing his goals and dreams in life,  while we finish many dreadfully long errands  talking to my son,  while doing errands in the morning makes me look forward to starting them.  getting to know him and him getting to know me,  is one of the greatest things in life!  * i got the idea for the poem by a picture by van gogh called boulevard de clichy.

text: people knew about rain but never would tell  rain would cry all the time  but wipe it away by the bell  she is in a very dark place  where everything is miserable there are secrets untold  i really don't think that's livable  she has bruises left and right  when she comes home she gets beat when she cries the pain increases  when it's over she takes her seat   love is not a word  rain is crying all the time  but when no one loves you  life is not worth a dime   until one day little rain opens up she finally tells someone about her  they come and take her away  every thing seems to be a blur  little rain opens her eyes  she sees a happy face where everything shines rain loves this place   when things are good and well little rain finally feels love  she is finally happy  now she is flying like a dove  she doesn't cry or hurt  because now she is soaring  with the past behind her  she does feel happy, love and never hurting  little rain my dove you will always be loved

title: Winter Wonderland
author: julie
text: speeding down the mountain just waiting for the fall,  stops to wait and wonder who created this all?  snow falling peacefully to her left and right,  wind whipping in her face her sister starting a fight,   wind strewn hair is dancing all around deep hazel eyes begin to water,  a piercing glare resonating off the ground parents forgetting about their daughter,   taken aback by curiosity who? what? where? when? and why!? sitting down to take a break staring at the big blue sky,   no stopping,  no time to waste days are getting shorter must continue with much haste not enough time on these winter days.
